title.narrative: Fourth East West Highway Improvement Project

description.narrative: The PDOs are: (i) to contribute to the gradual reduction of road transport costs and to improve road safety along the section upgraded under the project; and (ii) to strengthen the capacity of the Roads Department (RD) and Ministry of Regional Development and Infrastructure (MRDI) to plan and manage the road network and improve road traffic safety.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Action plan to implement mid term review recommendations | Description :Borrower shall, promptly following theMTR, prepare and action program, acceptable to the Bank, for the further implementation of the Project having due regard to thefindings of the MTR, and thereafter implement such program with due diligence and efficiency | Due Date :15-Jan-2016

Finance Agreement :Anti-corruption guidelines | Description :The borrower shall insure that the Project is carried out inaccordance with the provisions of the Anti-Corruption Guidelines | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Compliance with EMP, RAP and RPF | Description :The borrower shall ensure the Project is carried out inaccordance with EIA, EMP and RFP - Not assign, amend, abrogate or waive EIA, EMP, RFP, RAP or any provision - Improve road safetyprior to starting small scale work, ensure the preparation of site specific EMP, incorporate this is the design and includes thesein proposed work contracts | Frequency :Quarterly
Finance Agreement :Effectiveness | Description :Borower has submitted to the Bank the OM in form and substance satisfactory to theBank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
Finance Agreement :Mid term review | Description :Carry out MTR by reviewing progress | Due Date :15-Dec-2015
Finance Agreement :Site specific EMPs for road safety works | Description :tbd | Frequency :Quarterly
Finance Agreement :Staff and Resources | Description :The borrower shall maintain the RD with adequate staff and resources, in amanner satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
